In[62]:
df_combined = pd.concat([df_ford, df_tesla, df_chevrolet, df_toyota, df_nissan, df_honda, df_bmw, df_mercedes, df_volkswagen])
df_combined['Date'] = pd.to_datetime(df_combined['Date'], utc=True)
cutoff_date = pd.Timestamp("2010-06-29 00:00:00-04:00")

df_combined = df_combined[df_combined["Date"] > cutoff_date]
df_combined["Month-Day"] = df_combined["Date"].dt.strftime("%m-%d")
def assign_season(month_day):
    if month_day < "03-20":
        return "Winter"
    elif month_day < "06-21":
        return "Spring"
    elif month_day < "09-22":
        return "Summer"
    elif month_day < "12-21":
        return "Fall"
    else:
        return "Winter"

# Apply the function to the "Month-Day" column
df_combined["Season"] = df_combined["Month-Day"].apply(assign_season)
df_combined.drop(columns=["Return", "LogReturn", "Month"], inplace=True)
df_combined.head()
df_combined['Year'] = df_combined['Date'].dt.year

Modeling

In[64]:
from sklearn.compose import make_column_transformer
from sklearn.pipeline import make_pipeline
from sklearn.preprocessing import StandardScaler, OneHotEncoder
from sklearn.neighbors import KNeighborsRegressor
from sklearn.model_selection import cross_val_score
from sklearn.model_selection import GridSearchCV
from sklearn.model_selection import train_test_split

known = df_seasonal_avg['Year'] <= 2021
unknown = df_seasonal_avg['Year'] > 2021
df_train = df_seasonal_avg[known]
df_test = df_seasonal_avg[unknown]

x_train = df_train.drop(columns=["Close"])
y_train = df_train["Close"]
x_test = df_test.drop(columns=["Close"])
y_test = df_test["Close"]


quant = ["High", "Low", "Volume", "Year"]
cat = ["Company", "Season"]

ct = make_column_transformer(
    (StandardScaler(), quant),
    (OneHotEncoder(handle_unknown="ignore"), cat)
)

pipeline = make_pipeline(
    ct,
    KNeighborsRegressor()
)

grid_cv = GridSearchCV(
    estimator=pipeline,
    param_grid = {
    "kneighborsregressor__n_neighbors": range(1, 30),
    "kneighborsregressor__metric": ["euclidean", "manhattan"]},
    scoring="neg_root_mean_squared_error",
    cv=5,
    return_train_score=True
)

grid_cv.fit(x_train, y_train)

grid_cv.best_params_

In[65]:
best_params = grid_cv.best_params_

final_model = make_pipeline(
    ct,
    KNeighborsRegressor(
        n_neighbors=best_params["kneighborsregressor__n_neighbors"],
        metric=best_params["kneighborsregressor__metric"],
    )
)

final_model.fit(x_train, y_train)

y_pred = final_model.predict(x_test)

results_df = x_test.copy()
results_df["Actual Close"] = y_test
results_df["Predicted Close"] = y_pred

Finding accuracy of each company across each season

In[66]:
# USE THIS CODE CHUNK TO FIGURE OUT ERROR / ACCURACY OF MODEL
from sklearn.metrics import mean_squared_error, mean_absolute_error, r2_score

results_df["se"] = (results_df["Predicted Close"] - results_df["Actual Close"])**2
from sklearn.metrics import mean_squared_error, r2_score

mse = mean_squared_error(results_df["Actual Close"], results_df["Predicted Close"])
r2 = r2_score(results_df["Actual Close"], results_df["Predicted Close"])

company_metrics = results_df.groupby("Company").apply(
    lambda group: pd.Series({
        "mse": mean_squared_error(group["Actual Close"], group["Predicted Close"]),
        "r2": r2_score(group["Actual Close"], group["Predicted Close"])
    })
).reset_index()

from sklearn.cluster import KMeans
from sklearn.pipeline import make_pipeline

features = ["Open", "High", "Low", "Close", "Volume"]

model = KMeans(n_clusters = 9, random_state = 1234)

pipeline = make_pipeline(
    StandardScaler(),
    model
)

pipeline.fit(df_combined[features]);

clusters = model.labels_
centroids = model.cluster_centers_
